<TEXT>
JONATHAN Davies, who has played only twice for Cardiff since his return to
union from rugby league club Warrington earlier this month, faces an operation
that could scupper his return to Five Nations' Championship action.
Wales' disappointing performance in last Saturday's 19-15 win over Fiji
increased the calls for his return to the national side.
``I think I popped a hernia against Cambridge University,'' said Davies. ``But
having had this sort of injury before, I know the form - which is to rest for a
week before starting light running and then I should be playing again in three
weeks to a month.''
