<HEADLINE>SNOOKER Five for Burnett</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>39</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975355995</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SNOOKER
SCOTLAND'S Alan Burnett yesterday made it five wins out of five when he ended
English champion David Gray's unbeaten run with a 4-2 victory in the Embassy
IBSF World amateur championship at Q's Club in Bristol.
Burnett, reigning world junior champion, moved into a 2-0 lead over the
Londoner with breaks of 42 and 45. However Gray, at 16 the youngest ever
English champion, replied with 104 in the third frame. Ayrshire teenager
Burnett took the next, only for Gray to knock in an 83 to reduce the deficit to
3-2, but Burnett clinched the qualifying group match with a run of 71.
Alok Kumar, of India, produced the highest break of the tournament so far - a
142 clearance - in the opening frame of his match against New Zealand's Harry
Haenga, but still lost 4-1.
</TEXT>
