<TEXT>
RIDGEWOOD Pearl was crowned Horse of the Year at a gala dinner in London last
night to celebrate the fifth annual Cartier racing awards.
The Irish 1000 Guineas winner, who was also named three-year-old filly of the
year, won five of her six starts in 1995, culminating in the Breeders' Cup Mile
at Belmont last month.
Winners in other categories included Lammtarra, runner-up to Ridgewood Pearl as
Horse of the Year, Alhaarth and Double Trigger. Winners:
Two-year-old colt: Alhaarth. Two-year-old filly: Blue Duster. Three-year-old
colt: Lammtarra. Three-year-old filly: Ridgewood Pearl. Sprinter: Hever Golf
Rose. Stayer: Double Trigger. Older horse: Further Flight. Horse of the Year:
Ridgewood Pearl. Award of merit: John Dunlop.
