<TEXT>
q SCOTLAND avoided relegation from the top 16 with a 2-1 win over Austria in
yesterday's final section match at the world squash championships in Cairo.
Alan Thomson, the 35-year-old veteran, recovered to beat Christian Wind 5-9,
9-0, 9-5, 9-0 and the Scots now move into play-offs for places nine to 16.
England reached the last eight of the men's team championship - helped by
opponents, defending champions Pakistan, who chose to rest world champion
Jansher Khan.
Simon Parke beat replacement Zarak Jahan 9-7, 9-2, 9-3. Del Harris won 9-3,
9-0, 9-3 against Mir Zaman Gul but Chris Walker lost 2-9, 1-9, 9-2, 9-4, 9-1
to Zubair Jahan.
