<HEADLINE>CABLES BICC shakes up business</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>23</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975356023</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BICC has warned that it will be making rationalisation and closure provisions
of around #80m in 1995, mostly reflecting major rationalisations throughout its
cables business as it reduces costs and capacity in that sector.
The group is also in discussion with interested parties on the sale of its
housebuilding business. In the present depressed housing environment this is
likely to result in a loss against the book value of the assets. If the
business is sold, then for accounting purposes, goodwill written off on an
acquisition made in 1987, amounting to #44m, would also be shown as a charge
against profits.
</TEXT>
