<HEADLINE>Relatives in African court hear of gruesome attack on British couple by five-man gang Family told of machete murder</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>11</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>975356056</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Nairobi, Wednesday
THE husband and three other relatives of a British woman raped and hacked to
death in Kenya were in a Nairobi court today for the start of the trial of
three men accused of her horrific death.
Thirty-one-year-old Caron Winter's husband Adam later left the court and was
said by his brother, Harry, to be too upset to hear more of the gruesome
evidence.
Other relatives sat through the two-and-a-half hour session.
They heard how Londoner Mrs Winter was murdered at midday on July 31 last year
by what was believed to be a five-man gang wielding machetes, a hammer and
other weapons. Her 15-month-old daughter was just feet away in another room.
Mr Winter was beaten with a hammer and his nose was almost slashed off when he
arrived at their suburban Nairobi home during the attack.
He is expected to give evidence tomorrow after travelling from his new home on
the Caribbean island of Antigua for the trial.
The couple's neighbour in Nairobi, Phil Matthews, told the court: ``I found Mr
Winter with his baby in his arms. He was covered in blood.
``His nose had been cut from the top. There was a piece of his nose that was
hanging down.
``Caron Winter was lying on the floor. She was in a pool of blood,'' he added.
Security guards called to the scene identified goods stolen during the raid and
Mr Winter's brother Harry, from London, told how he had arrived in Kenya the
day after the killing to identify Caron's body.
``It was the worst experience of my life,'' he said outside the court.
With him were his mother, Ruth, and Caron Winter's brother Mr Adrian McDonald.
The Winters had been living in Kenya about a year before her death. She had
started a silk-screening business and Adam was a pilot who helped fly aid
missions for Rwandans after the genocide there.
Although prosecutor Horace Okumu told the court yesterday that Mrs Winter was
raped before she was killed, the three accused men are charged only with
murder.
Defendants Yusuf Rashid Wamasoro, James Washi-komba and Alexander Shikavale,
all Ugandans, have pleaded not guilty. All face death by hanging if convicted.
Today the hearing was halted when the judge announced that he does not sit in
the afternoons.-AP
</TEXT>
