<RECORDNO>975356070</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
I READ the report by Frances Horsburgh about Edinburgh's plans being streets
ahead, and the comments attributed to Colin Davis (November 14).
The Edinburgh document is not the pioneering document claimed as Strathclyde
region, in partnership with Glasgow District Council and Glasgow Development
Agency, has already published in February its Public Realm Strategy and
Guidelines for Glasgow City Centre.
In July 1994, Strathclyde also published two other relevant documents,
Streetscape - A Design Guide, and the Footways Development Guide.
Should readers be interested in obtaining a copy of these reports they should
contact the address at the foot of this letter.
Donald Carruthers,
Director,
Strathclyde Roads,
Richmond Exchange,
20 Cadogan Street,
Glasgow G2 7AD.
</TEXT>
