<HEADLINE>Honour for Sir Fitzroy Maclean</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975356125</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SIR Fitzroy Maclean, 84, is to be given the Freedom of Argyll. Argyll and Bute
District Council agreed to bestow the honour on the wartime hero at a meeting
in Lochgilphead yesterday. The honour is in recognition of his lifetime
achievements.
Councillor Robert Reid (Kyles and Bute) said: ``In the light of his outstanding
achievements and in particluar his efforts in Yugoslavia, he should be
recognised by the people of Argyll in this way.''
