<HEADLINE>Walter Galbraith</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>16</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Obituary</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975356128</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Walter Galbraith, former manager of Hibernian, has died, aged 77.
A player with Queen's Park, Clyde, and Grimsby in the forties, Galbraith took
charge of Hibs in the early sixties. He followed Hugh Shaw as manager of the
Edinburgh club in 1961 and stayed there until he was succeeded three years
later by Jock Stein.
Galbraith had spells as manager with Brighton, Accrington Stanley, Tranmere
Rovers and Stockport County. He leaves a wife and a son.
</TEXT>
