<DATE>951116</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Murder trial halted as jury is discharged</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>15</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975356131</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE trial of Gordon Wardell, accused of murdering his building society
manageress wife, was halted yesterday and the jury discharged.
Mr Wardell, 42, a car parts company executive from Meriden, Warwickshire,
denies murdering his wife Carol, who worked for the Woolwich Building Society,
in September last year.
The trial, which opened on Tuesday at Oxford Crown Court, came to an unexpected
stop after a female jury member disclosed information to court officials. The
judge, Mr Justice Cresswell, said: ``Juror 11 has very properly drawn to my
attention certain matters which are such that I must discharge her from further
services on this jury. I direct that she leave the building with my thanks.
``It follows from the discharge of that juror that I must discharge the rest of
you and invite you to leave the jury box and await further instructions.''
The trial, which is expected to last at least five weeks, is due to start again
today.
</TEXT>
